The cascade palette is a keyboard-driven command surface — a single window into actions, configuration, entities, and search that follows a small set of consistent gestures.

! Five gestures

|!Gesture |!Effect |
|`Ctrl-Space` |Open the palette anywhere. Resets to root if already open. |
|`→` |Drill — descend a tree container or push the action menu on a typed catalogue row. |
|`Space` |Open the action menu on any tiddler row with applicable actions (works in tree views too — see ''Action discovery''). |
|`Esc` |Pop the current stage. From root, closes the palette. |
|`↵` |Fire the selected row (or commit text). |

`Tab` cycles focus //between sections// (input → preset → filter → view → menu → details → …). `Shift-Tab` jumps between the pill-group (top strips) and the main group (input/menu/details/preview).

Everything else — pills, leaders, search reach, side preview, action menus — composes on top of these four.

! How sections compose

The palette has //facets// you can stack independently:

* ''Filters'' narrow the data set you're walking
* ''Reach'' widens search scope (current stage / whole tree)
* ''Search-in'' picks which fields the matcher reads
* ''Views'' switch between alternate trees of the same data
* ''Presets'' snapshot a whole configuration for one-keystroke recall

Each facet is a pill strip. Pills can be added (via leaders) and removed (DEL on a focused pill). No modal dialogs, no checkbox lists — just navigable pills.

